%N A394960 a(n) = (2^(n-1)-1) * (2^n-3).
%C A394960 For n > 0, number of ways to choose two distinct, nonempty proper subsets from a set of size n.
%C A394960 For n > 1, number of edges in the (2^n-3)-dimensional simplex.
%H A394960 <a href="/index/Rec#order_03">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (7,-14,8).
%F A394960 a(n) = binomial(2^n-2,2).
%F A394960 G.f.: (1-7*x+15*x^2) / ((1-x)*(1-2*x)*(1-4*x)).
%F A394960 E.g.f.: (1/2) * exp(x) * (exp(3*x)-5*exp(x)+6).
%F A394960 a(n) = A000225(n-1)*A036563(n).
